func_register_filter.name: register_filter
func_register_filter.docstring:
Decorator to register a filter function with metadata

Args:
    name: Display name for the filter
    category: Category for organization (e.g., "Color", "Brightness")
    description: User-friendly description
    has_intensity: Whether filter supports intensity control
    min_intensity: Minimum intensity value (default: 0.0)
    max_intensity: Maximum intensity value (default: 1.0)
    default_intensity: Default intensity value (default: 0.5)
    preview_available: Whether preview is available (default: False)

Returns:
    Decorated filter function
    
Example:
    @register_filter(
        name="Grayscale",
        category="Color",
        description="Convert to black and white",
        has_intensity=True
    )
    def apply_grayscale(clip, intensity=1.0):
        return clip.fx(vfx.blackwhite)
